comments.text:
TRANSLATION 

- Of course, the man of the match could only be you, the GOAT.
- Leo, let me ask you, because you were coming back from an injury. The president, Jorge Mas, said you weren't 100%, that you were still injured. How did you manage to play like this today?
  - “Well, I wanted to play since I came back against Galaxy, but I felt some discomfort, I wasn’t comfortable. I prepared myself specifically for this match because I knew how important the rival was; a very tough rival who we hadn’t beaten this year in our previous encounters. Honestly, in the first half, I still had a little fear, but in the second, I loosened up a lot more.”
- And do you feel okay now?
  - “Yes, I ended well. Tired, like the whole team. It was very hot, very humid, the usual. But happy, happy to reach the final.”

- The Leagues Cup is a special tournament for you because it’s where you made your debut and became the top scorer. What does it mean to reach another Leagues Cup final in 2025?
  - “I said it from the first match: this is a group that competes. We showed it in the CONCACAF Champions League, where we got knocked out by Vancouver in the semifinals. For this Leagues Cup, we said from the beginning that we were going to fight for it. I was unlucky to miss half a match, but the group made a huge sacrifice. We played against really strong teams, like Tigres, which is an amazing team, one of the best in Mexico with very good players and a strong squad. At home, we’re strong, and now we have to play away, whoever the opponent is, but we’re in the final.”

- Leo, you’ve played many derbies in your career, but what does it mean to finally beat Orlando City after those heavy defeats, 3-0 and 4-1?
  - “Yes, it’s special. It’s always special to play a derby. As I said before, Orlando is a great rival with very good players. They’re a well-organized team with a coach who’s been working with the same group for years. It was a small revenge for us after those two losses in the league. Luckily, I got to play it again in the Leagues Cup and win, and today we knocked them out once more. So, yes, it’s special.”

- Last question: Argentina plays Venezuela in September, and people say it might be your last World Cup qualifier in Buenos Aires. Are you experiencing it that way?
  - “Yes, it’s going to be special. It will be a very special match for me because it’s the last qualifier. I don’t know if there’ll be any friendlies or more matches after, but yes, it’s a very special match. That’s why my family, my wife, my children, my parents, my brothers, and everyone who can will be there—also my wife’s family. We will experience it that way. After that, I don’t know what will happen, but we go into it with that intention.”
- Thank you, Leo. Congratulations.
- Thank you. Bye. Thank you.
